# Add Canvas Planning Tool to Debts

We will add a dedicated canvas planning space to each individual debt. This allows you to plan repayment strategies (like brainstorming extra payments, visualization, attaching notes, etc.) exactly like you do for assets.

## Open Questions
- Do you want to restrict the canvas to specific types of debts, or should all active debts have the "Plan" button? (The plan assumes all active debts get the button).
- Should the new page be named "Debt Plan Canvas" or "Debt Roadmap Canvas"? (The plan assumes "Debt Plan Canvas").

## Proposed Changes

### Database & Backend Models
#### [MODIFY] app/models/finance.py
- Add a new column `plan_canvas_data` of type `JSON` to the `Debt` model.

#### [NEW] Database Migration
- Run `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add plan_canvas_data to debts"` to apply the schema change.

### API Schemas
#### [MODIFY] app/schemas/finance.py
- Add `plan_canvas_data: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None` to the following schemas:
  - `DebtBase`
  - `DebtUpdate`
  - `DebtResponse`

### Frontend Application
#### [NEW] src/pages/finance/debts/DebtPlanPage.tsx
- Create a new page component that:
  - Fetches a specific debt by ID.
  - Renders the existing `AssetRoadmapCanvas` component, passing the `debt.plan_canvas_data`.
  - Implements an `onSave` handler to `PUT` the updated canvas data back to the `/api/v1/debts/:id` endpoint.
  - Includes a header that shows the debt name and a back button to return to the Debts dashboard.

#### [MODIFY] src/App.tsx
- Register the new route: `<Route path="/finance/debts/:id/plan" element={<DebtPlanPage />} />`

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/finance/debts/DebtsPage.tsx
- Inside the "Active Debts" list renderer (the middle column), add a new "Plan" button (using an icon like `Map` or `GitMerge`) next to or under the debt details.
- Clicking the button will navigate the user to `/finance/debts/${debt.id}/plan`.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- No new automated tests are required unless requested.

### Manual Verification
- Start the frontend and backend servers.
- Navigate to the Debts page.
- Verify the "Plan" button appears on the active debt cards.
- Click "Plan" and ensure it routes correctly to the new Canvas page.
- Add nodes/edges to the canvas and wait for the auto-save to trigger.
- Refresh the page to verify the canvas data persists correctly in the database.
